WEBVTT

00:06.257 --> 00:07.883
[Midge] I met him in the park.

00:07.967 --> 00:09.301
I always walk Ethan
through the park

00:09.385 --> 00:10.678
on the way to kindergarten.

00:10.761 --> 00:12.304
It gives us
a little time together,

00:12.388 --> 00:13.848
and I love the fresh air.

00:13.931 --> 00:16.392
His dog said hello first.

00:16.475 --> 00:18.144
Then he said hello.

00:18.227 --> 00:20.479
♪ Autumn in New York...

00:20.563 --> 00:22.022
And I liked him.

00:22.106 --> 00:23.315
Pretty instantly.

00:23.399 --> 00:25.651
He was good-looking, smart.

00:25.735 --> 00:27.111
You can tell by the eyes.

00:27.194 --> 00:28.821
I apologized
for kidnapping his pooch,

00:28.904 --> 00:31.282
and he flashed
this amazing smile.

00:31.365 --> 00:34.744
From then on,
we ran into him a lot.

00:34.827 --> 00:36.162
Pretty much every day.

00:36.245 --> 00:38.622
Pretty much on purpose.

00:38.706 --> 00:42.334
- ♪ ♪
- [dialogue inaudible]

00:42.418 --> 00:45.921
One time he brought me a flower
he picked along the way.

00:46.005 --> 00:48.799
It was pretty. He was pretty.

00:48.883 --> 00:50.676
The flirting was pretty intense
from both sides.

00:50.760 --> 00:51.761
- [children squealing]
- [Susie] Hold it.

00:51.844 --> 00:54.013
All morning,
this has been going on.

00:54.096 --> 00:57.433
- [laughing]
- I only talked to him because
he phoned and I picked up.

00:57.516 --> 00:58.893
How could I know not to pick up

00:58.976 --> 01:00.394
- when I don't know
it's him calling?
- Dinah.

01:00.478 --> 01:02.313
That's dumb, Frank. You're
being dumb. Don't be dumb.

01:02.396 --> 01:05.608
- Dinah.
- Hold on. Alfie's tech
rehearsal is all set for 12:30.

01:05.691 --> 01:06.901
- [door closes]
- That was my boss.

01:06.984 --> 01:08.235
It was my boss!

01:08.319 --> 01:09.695
- Dinah, hang up.
- Talk to him?

01:09.779 --> 01:11.030
He'll hang up
if he knows I'm at work.

01:11.113 --> 01:12.698
- He thinks I'm with Hank.
- This isn't Hank?

01:12.782 --> 01:14.283
It's Frank.
Hank's my other boyfriend.

01:14.366 --> 01:15.493
Christ. Hank.

01:15.618 --> 01:17.203
- Frank.
- Frank, Dinah's at work.

01:17.286 --> 01:19.288
Go away.

01:19.330 --> 01:20.623
- Satisfied?
- [door opens]

01:20.706 --> 01:22.917
No, that wasn't a man.
It was my boss, Susie.

01:23.000 --> 01:24.418
- [door closes]
- She's a woman!

01:24.502 --> 01:26.921
I'm done talking to you, Frank.
Goodbye.

01:27.004 --> 01:28.380
- [phone slams in cradle]
- Continue.

01:28.464 --> 01:31.091
One day, Ethan had
a day off from school.

01:31.175 --> 01:34.720
Zelda stayed with the kids,
and I hit the park by myself,

01:34.804 --> 01:36.013
hoping to run into him.

01:36.096 --> 01:37.848
And I did.

01:37.932 --> 01:40.226
♪ It's autumn in New York...

01:40.309 --> 01:42.394
This time,
we sat and talked for an hour.

01:42.478 --> 01:44.980
He told me about his work,
his hobbies,

01:45.064 --> 01:46.899
his love of French films.

01:46.982 --> 01:48.859
I was sure about it.

01:48.943 --> 01:50.528
This time, he's asking me out.

01:50.611 --> 01:54.365
And I did everything I could
to encourage it.

01:54.448 --> 01:56.450
But he never pulled the trigger.

01:56.534 --> 01:58.786
I thought about asking him out,
but I haven't asked out a guy

01:58.869 --> 02:01.455
since that disastrous experience
on Sadie Hawkins Day.

02:01.539 --> 02:02.498
[Susie] Wait, wait, wait.

02:02.581 --> 02:04.124
What the hell is
Sadie Hawkins Day?

02:04.208 --> 02:05.960
The day where the girls
ask out the boys.

02:06.043 --> 02:09.463
And I was all ready to ask
Jacob Fineman to the big dance.

02:09.547 --> 02:11.465
God, was I in love with him.

02:11.549 --> 02:15.135
That day, I'm standing outside
the temple with two RC Colas,

02:15.219 --> 02:18.055
and he's walking towards me
in his brand-new...

02:18.138 --> 02:20.683
Hold it! Do not start telling
a different goddamn story!

02:20.766 --> 02:21.767
There's no time.

02:21.851 --> 02:22.935
Fine.

02:23.018 --> 02:24.854
So, this morning,
I'm back in the park,

02:24.937 --> 02:26.021
without Ethan.

02:26.146 --> 02:27.064
And there he is,

02:27.147 --> 02:28.566
without his dog.

02:28.649 --> 02:31.652
This time, he tells me
how much he loves coffee.

02:31.735 --> 02:33.195
Said there was a place nearby

02:33.279 --> 02:35.406
that had the best espresso
in the city.

02:35.489 --> 02:37.283
And he asked me
if I was up for some.

02:37.366 --> 02:39.076
I said, "Now?"

02:39.159 --> 02:41.245
And he said, "Now."

02:41.328 --> 02:43.455
So he led the way.

02:43.539 --> 02:45.082
But the place was closed.

02:45.165 --> 02:46.959
They were remodeling
or something.

02:47.042 --> 02:48.669
Just my luck.

02:48.752 --> 02:51.422
Then he said he has a great
espresso machine at his place

02:51.505 --> 02:53.340
that he imported
all the way from Naples,

02:53.424 --> 02:55.384
and it's just around the corner.

02:55.467 --> 02:56.594
Oh, boy.

02:56.677 --> 02:58.554
I have never done this,
but I thought,

02:58.637 --> 03:00.472
"You only live once, Midge."

03:00.556 --> 03:01.891
And I was wearing
some nice underwear,

03:01.974 --> 03:03.267
so what the hell?

03:03.350 --> 03:04.768
He led the way.

03:04.852 --> 03:05.853
[♪ Ella Fitzgerald:
"You've Got What Gets Me"]

03:05.936 --> 03:07.938
Things happened fast after that.

03:10.482 --> 03:11.400
[whoops]

03:11.483 --> 03:12.818
It had been a while.

03:12.902 --> 03:14.403
Not since Benjamin.

03:14.486 --> 03:16.739
I felt a kind of catharsis.

03:16.822 --> 03:18.949
The thrill of spontaneity.

03:19.033 --> 03:22.036
I realized that I hadn't been
spontaneous enough in my life.

03:22.119 --> 03:24.914
Too much stop, not enough go.

03:24.997 --> 03:27.041
And I realized
that I liked this feeling,

03:27.124 --> 03:30.127
and I wanted
to keep feeling this feeling.

03:30.210 --> 03:31.921
- But then...
- [woman shrieks]

03:32.004 --> 03:34.882
- [gasps]
- Complete chaos.
- Oh, my God. Oh, my God!

03:34.965 --> 03:36.842
- Are you goddamn kidding me?
- [barking]

03:36.926 --> 03:38.761
- The hell are you doing here?
- What am I doing here?

03:38.844 --> 03:40.638
Who is this?
Some slut from the steno pool?

03:40.721 --> 03:42.222
She is not from the steno pool!

03:42.306 --> 03:43.891
[Midge] The guy's married.

03:43.974 --> 03:45.559
He's yelling, she's yelling,

03:45.643 --> 03:47.853
the dog is barking
its head off, and I'm stuck.

03:47.937 --> 03:50.648
I'm completely naked and there's
only one way out of the room

03:50.731 --> 03:52.900
and my clothes
are nowhere near me.

03:52.983 --> 03:54.860
So I grabbed what I could
and ran.

03:54.944 --> 03:57.029
I could still hear them yelling
at each other from the cab.

03:57.112 --> 04:00.032
- It was insane.
- You know what, draw up a list
of every guy you slept with!

04:00.115 --> 04:01.951
Otherwise, we're gonna be here
all goddamn day.

04:03.327 --> 04:04.620
Okay. So?

04:04.703 --> 04:05.913
What do you think?

04:05.996 --> 04:08.666
I want my goddamn dress back.

04:08.749 --> 04:10.501
♪ ♪

04:10.584 --> 04:12.378
[indistinct chatter]

04:12.461 --> 04:14.171
Walk like it's
just an everyday thing.

04:14.254 --> 04:16.173
Cool and casual, like
you're heading to the subway.

04:16.256 --> 04:18.050
Darn, I was gonna skip
like a schoolgirl.

04:18.133 --> 04:19.593
- Arch.
- I got this. Relax.

04:19.677 --> 04:21.470
A block and a half down.
North side of the street.

04:21.553 --> 04:22.972
- I know where it is.
- Ask for Cheng.

04:23.055 --> 04:24.807
He's the best teller
and he speaks English.

04:24.890 --> 04:26.976
- He does all my deposits.
- You already said that.

04:27.059 --> 04:28.602
I just don't like cash
sitting around the club,

04:28.686 --> 04:30.479
and I haven't found
my good hiding spots yet.

04:30.562 --> 04:31.605
The desk is too obvious.

04:31.689 --> 04:32.856
Everyone looks
in the booze crates.

04:32.940 --> 04:34.775
The rats can get to it
in the rafters.

04:34.858 --> 04:36.485
I think I'm gonna have to
jackhammer a hole in the floor

04:36.568 --> 04:37.611
and then hide it with a rug.

04:37.695 --> 04:38.946
And, yes,
I've just become my mother.

04:39.029 --> 04:40.614
Go back inside. I got this.

04:40.698 --> 04:41.865
Okay, thanks.

04:41.949 --> 04:43.701
- See you tonight.
- See you tonight.

04:43.784 --> 04:45.536
[engine roaring]

04:49.665 --> 04:50.708
Hey!

04:50.791 --> 04:53.502
[jackhammering]

04:53.585 --> 04:55.379
Oh, my. That's wonderful.

04:55.462 --> 04:56.839
I'll take two ounces of that.

04:56.922 --> 04:58.507
Great choice.
It's our most aromatic blend.

04:58.590 --> 05:00.217
I'm going to look around
a bit more,

05:00.300 --> 05:02.594
maybe pick up some cigars
for the boys at the office.

05:02.678 --> 05:04.471
I'll wrap this up for you.

05:04.555 --> 05:08.809
[man] Yes, well, uh, we have
a fine, fine cigar...

05:08.892 --> 05:11.270
Good morning, sir.
Are you enjoying your day?

05:11.353 --> 05:12.604
Very much. Thank you.

05:12.688 --> 05:15.065
And there's more days
you'd like to enjoy?

05:15.149 --> 05:16.692
I beg your pardon?

05:16.775 --> 05:18.777
I insist on feeding my family.

05:18.861 --> 05:20.487
So when my livelihood
is threatened,

05:20.571 --> 05:22.072
I threaten back.

05:22.156 --> 05:23.949
That's understandable.

05:24.033 --> 05:25.701
There's a line in the Torah:

05:25.784 --> 05:27.786
"fuck with me and you die."

05:27.870 --> 05:30.247
Have a think on this.

05:30.330 --> 05:32.291
I will. But, for now,

05:32.374 --> 05:34.668
I'm going to move
to another part of the store.

05:34.752 --> 05:36.628
Nice talking to you.

05:36.712 --> 05:39.298
[man] This one has a really nice
frame and shape to it.

05:39.381 --> 05:41.133
- Hello to you, sir.
- Hello.

05:41.216 --> 05:42.885
Oh, do you have a moment?

05:42.968 --> 05:46.346
I'd like to discuss matchmaking.

05:46.430 --> 05:47.890
Oh. Sure.

05:47.973 --> 05:49.892
It's got quite
the lively history.

05:49.975 --> 05:53.145
The first matches date back
to 14th century China.

05:53.228 --> 05:55.272
They dipped pine sticks
in sulfur...

05:55.355 --> 05:59.443
I meant the kind
your bony wife is engaged in.

05:59.526 --> 06:01.612
- My...
- You're Abe Weissman,
aren't you?

06:01.695 --> 06:03.155
Husband of Rose,

06:03.238 --> 06:05.032
father to Miriam,

06:05.115 --> 06:09.787
grandfather to Ethan,
Esther and Chaim.

06:09.870 --> 06:13.540
Oh, you know, I have nothing
to do with what my wife does.

06:13.624 --> 06:16.627
But you have influence.

06:16.710 --> 06:17.920
You're the man, aren't you?

06:18.003 --> 06:19.129
I suppose.

06:19.213 --> 06:21.507
Unless we take your manhood
from you.

06:21.590 --> 06:23.092
Who are you?

06:23.175 --> 06:24.384
Doesn't matter.

06:24.468 --> 06:25.886
Just tell your wife to stop.

06:25.969 --> 06:28.055
- Stop.
- Stop now.

06:28.138 --> 06:29.556
Stop? Sure.

06:29.640 --> 06:32.392
Uh, could you just answer
one little question for me?

06:32.476 --> 06:35.562
- Yes.
- Are there any more of you
outside?

06:35.646 --> 06:37.147
Just us.

06:37.231 --> 06:40.067
♪ ♪

06:40.150 --> 06:43.237
- Sir! Your tobacco!
- Keep it!

06:43.320 --> 06:46.115
- [♪ The Everly Brothers:
"So Sad (to Watch Love Go Bad)"]
- ♪ We used to have ♪

06:46.198 --> 06:49.493
♪ Good times together...

06:49.576 --> 06:50.786
You already ordered?

06:50.869 --> 06:52.371
- Yeah.
- Why?

06:52.454 --> 06:54.498
Well, you're late and I have
to be at Susie's at 11:00,

06:54.581 --> 06:55.666
so I ordered for both of us.

06:55.749 --> 06:57.584
It's ice-cold.
And you're always late.

06:57.668 --> 06:59.461
Except today.

06:59.545 --> 07:01.421
I don't even want this.
I just want eggs.

07:01.505 --> 07:02.506
Then get some eggs.

07:02.589 --> 07:04.383
And throw all this away,
like I'm Henry VIII?

07:04.466 --> 07:06.760
Yes. Just don't behead me.

07:08.262 --> 07:09.721
Want to go out
and come back in again?

07:09.805 --> 07:12.224
No. It's just...

07:12.307 --> 07:13.809
everything's crazy.

07:13.892 --> 07:15.060
- I know.
- That bag of cash.

07:15.144 --> 07:17.146
I never should've trusted it
to Archie.

07:17.229 --> 07:20.357
- It wasn't his fault.
- He was holding it like
it was takeout from Junior's.

07:20.440 --> 07:21.525
So amateur.

07:21.608 --> 07:22.609
You want me to question Imogene,

07:22.693 --> 07:23.902
see if it was an inside job?

07:23.986 --> 07:25.362
It's gonna make money tight.

07:25.445 --> 07:27.197
We'll figure it out.

07:27.281 --> 07:29.283
Excuse me. Could we get
three eggs scrambled

07:29.366 --> 07:31.160
- and some fresh coffee?
- You got it.

07:31.243 --> 07:33.662
Here. From Ma and Pop.

07:33.745 --> 07:35.539
Potential Halloween costumes
for the kids.

07:35.622 --> 07:37.207
Ladies at the factory
worked 'em up.

07:40.377 --> 07:42.254
- Now what?
- Bonnie and Clyde.

07:42.337 --> 07:43.505
Romeo and Juliet.

07:43.589 --> 07:45.549
- These are couples.
- So?

07:45.632 --> 07:47.176
Couples who...

07:47.259 --> 07:48.177
you know.

07:48.260 --> 07:49.636
Ew. Don't even imply that.

07:49.720 --> 07:50.637
It's our children.

07:50.721 --> 07:51.763
Tarzan and Jane?

07:51.847 --> 07:53.432
You really want to put
your son in a loincloth?

07:53.515 --> 07:55.017
What is with you today?

07:55.100 --> 07:56.894
What is with you?

08:00.105 --> 08:01.481
Is it just the money?

08:01.565 --> 08:03.734
Yes. Of course. Just the money.

08:03.817 --> 08:04.985
Only you would say
"just the money."

08:05.068 --> 08:06.320
Joel.

08:06.403 --> 08:08.071
[sighs]

08:08.155 --> 08:10.866
♪ When I know for certain...

08:10.949 --> 08:12.409
[exhales] We're having a baby.

08:12.492 --> 08:14.036
Who is?

08:14.119 --> 08:15.329
Me and Mei.

08:15.412 --> 08:17.873
We're having a baby.

08:17.956 --> 08:19.291
Wow.

08:20.292 --> 08:21.293
Wow.

08:21.376 --> 08:22.961
Add a couple of hundred wows
for me.

08:23.045 --> 08:24.630
I assume it was a surprise?

08:24.713 --> 08:25.631
You could say that.

08:25.714 --> 08:27.466
Anything else?

08:30.344 --> 08:32.137
- So what's the plan?
- It's brand-new.

08:32.221 --> 08:33.889
- That's not a plan.
- We just found out.

08:33.972 --> 08:35.057
Again, not a plan.

08:35.140 --> 08:36.058
What do you want to know, Midge?

08:36.141 --> 08:37.142
The color of the nursery?

08:37.226 --> 08:38.143
Which college it's going to?

08:38.227 --> 08:40.145
I get to know something, Joel.

08:40.229 --> 08:42.022
This is gonna affect me
and the kids a lot.

08:42.105 --> 08:43.232
- I know.
- I mean,

08:43.315 --> 08:44.942
- what have you discussed?
- Nothing.

08:45.025 --> 08:47.319
She's not even here. She's
interviewing for her residency.

08:47.402 --> 08:49.404
- Out of town?
- Yeah.

08:49.488 --> 08:51.990
What happens if she lands
somewhere else? Do you move?

08:52.074 --> 08:53.450
I've got the club.
You know I can't move.

08:53.533 --> 08:54.701
Does she know that?

08:54.785 --> 08:56.286
You know,
I didn't have to tell you this.

08:56.370 --> 08:58.163
That my kids
are gonna have a stepmom?

08:58.247 --> 08:59.873
- Really?
I didn't need to know this?
- These are cold.

08:59.957 --> 09:01.291
I'd find out
when I run into the two of you

09:01.375 --> 09:02.501
pushing a stroller?

09:02.584 --> 09:04.503
You know, forget this.

09:04.586 --> 09:05.545
Forget we ever spoke.

09:05.629 --> 09:07.631
Joel, wait!

09:15.430 --> 09:17.099
You can't be mad at me
for asking questions.

09:17.182 --> 09:19.309
Those aren't questions. They're
the fucking third degree.

09:19.393 --> 09:22.271
I know nothing about this girl
except she's gonna be a doctor.

09:22.354 --> 09:23.939
- That's right.
- What kind of doctor?

09:24.022 --> 09:26.650
Foot doctor? Brain doctor?
Eye doctor? Kid doctor?

09:26.733 --> 09:27.943
Just a doctor doctor.

09:28.026 --> 09:29.486
You seem to know nothing
about this girl.

09:29.569 --> 09:31.321
Does she even have a last name?
Doctor what?

09:31.405 --> 09:33.240
- Lin.
- One "N" or two?

09:33.323 --> 09:34.283
One.

09:34.366 --> 09:35.701
You had to think about it?

09:35.784 --> 09:37.411
She'll change her name
to Maisel.

09:37.494 --> 09:38.870
So you're getting married?

09:38.954 --> 09:40.539
Would it kill you
to be happy for me?

09:40.622 --> 09:42.791
- You need to be happy first.
- I'm happy.

09:42.874 --> 09:45.419
Okay? I'm happy! This is happy!

09:45.502 --> 09:47.379
When are you telling
Moishe and Shirley?

09:47.462 --> 09:49.339
- How do you know I haven't?
- Because I was on the phone

09:49.423 --> 09:50.716
with Shirley
for half an hour last night,

09:50.799 --> 09:52.467
and the bulk of the conversation
was about instant yeast

09:52.551 --> 09:54.136
and that sexy Robert Goulet.

09:54.219 --> 09:55.679
They don't know yet.
So don't say anything.

09:55.762 --> 09:57.514
She may be showing
the next time they see her.

09:57.597 --> 09:59.016
They haven't met her yet.

09:59.099 --> 10:00.267
They hav...

10:00.350 --> 10:01.893
Do you have a handle on this?

10:01.977 --> 10:02.978
At all?

10:03.061 --> 10:04.438
God,

10:04.521 --> 10:06.565
Joel, what have
you gotten yourself into?

10:06.648 --> 10:08.608
I want to get off this street.

10:08.692 --> 10:10.652
Are you really getting married?

10:11.695 --> 10:14.197
She and I are gonna work out the
logistics when she gets back.

10:14.281 --> 10:15.699
I will keep you in the loop.

10:15.782 --> 10:17.659
And prospective parents
tend to get married.

10:17.743 --> 10:20.620
- Okay.
- Don't mention this to anyone
till I say you can.

10:20.704 --> 10:21.872
Yes, sir.

10:21.955 --> 10:23.540
That wasn't a command.

10:24.541 --> 10:26.001
I'll see you later.

10:26.084 --> 10:27.502
And I'll talk to Pop
about the costumes.

10:27.586 --> 10:29.254
[clang]

10:36.136 --> 10:37.220
- Abe?
- [panting]

10:37.304 --> 10:38.847
Away from the door.
Away from the door.

10:38.930 --> 10:40.682
- Why?
- Is that back door locked?

10:40.766 --> 10:42.768
Yes. What's wrong?
You're sweating.

10:42.851 --> 10:44.978
Quiet. Whisper.
Mime it if you can.

10:45.062 --> 10:46.897
- Abe.
- The little one, Rose.

10:46.980 --> 10:48.398
- The little one.
- What little one?

10:48.482 --> 10:50.609
The tiny Jewish one.
Moloch in pearls.

10:50.692 --> 10:54.404
The big one.
Irish, with hands that crush.

10:54.488 --> 10:55.655
They were in the store.

10:55.739 --> 10:56.656
What store?

10:56.740 --> 10:57.908
My tobacco store.

10:57.991 --> 10:59.910
Apparently, you're a matchmaker?

10:59.993 --> 11:01.536
Abe, I've been a matchmaker
all these months.

11:01.620 --> 11:02.746
You knew that.

11:02.829 --> 11:04.122
Well, they're matchmakers, too.

11:04.206 --> 11:06.375
And they want you to stop.

11:06.458 --> 11:08.877
That's what they said.
In no uncertain terms

11:08.960 --> 11:10.796
and intimidating accents.

11:10.879 --> 11:11.922
Stop.

11:12.005 --> 11:13.507
Your coat is ripped.
Did they hurt you?

11:13.590 --> 11:18.387
No. But I was afraid they
would follow me from the store,

11:18.470 --> 11:20.806
so I did everything I could
to shake them.

11:20.889 --> 11:23.517
I serpentined my way
through streets,

11:23.600 --> 11:25.310
ran into random shops,

11:25.394 --> 11:27.437
- dove between cars.
- Oh, my God.

11:27.521 --> 11:28.814
Then I...

11:30.982 --> 11:32.025
Abe?

11:32.109 --> 11:33.151
I...

11:33.235 --> 11:35.195
- You what?
- [bell tolling]

11:35.278 --> 11:37.406
[Abe] I ducked
into a Catholic church,

11:37.489 --> 11:39.032
thinking sanctuary,

11:39.116 --> 11:41.034
at least from the Irish one.

11:41.118 --> 11:42.869
I thought it would be empty,

11:42.953 --> 11:44.538
but they were in the middle
of mass.

11:44.621 --> 11:49.042
The only sound in the room
was this windy pipe organ.

11:49.126 --> 11:51.336
[organ playing]

11:51.420 --> 11:54.089
There was a long line of people
headed up the aisle,

11:54.172 --> 11:56.550
so I joined it.

11:56.633 --> 11:58.343
I had no idea what it was for.

11:58.427 --> 12:00.804
I just moved along with it.

12:00.887 --> 12:02.180
Blend in--

12:02.264 --> 12:04.307
that was the strategy.

12:05.350 --> 12:06.518
When I got to the front,

12:06.601 --> 12:08.603
everyone was kneeling.

12:08.687 --> 12:11.064
So I knelt, too.

12:12.149 --> 12:14.234
That's when I saw him.

12:14.317 --> 12:16.653
He was holding this silver cup.

12:16.736 --> 12:19.823
And in order
not to look suspicious...

12:19.906 --> 12:21.074
Abe,

12:21.158 --> 12:23.034
- you didn't.
- I took communion.

12:23.118 --> 12:24.953
- Oh, my God.
- I think the priest

12:25.036 --> 12:26.037
was suspicious.

12:26.121 --> 12:28.457
Especially when he said,
"The body of Christ"

12:28.540 --> 12:29.958
and I answered, "Mazel tov."

12:30.041 --> 12:30.959
My head is spinning.

12:31.042 --> 12:31.960
So, there I was,

12:32.043 --> 12:33.378
with a mouthful of Christ,

12:33.462 --> 12:35.422
wondering what the hell to do.

12:35.505 --> 12:38.008
I left immediately
and took it out.

12:38.091 --> 12:40.510
And now...

12:40.594 --> 12:42.471
what do I do with it?

12:42.554 --> 12:44.306
Wrap it up in something.
Set it aside.

12:44.389 --> 12:46.516
- We've got bigger worries.
- They mentioned Miriam

12:46.600 --> 12:48.643
and the grandchildren by name.

12:48.727 --> 12:51.563
Go clean up.
We will figure this out.

12:57.277 --> 12:59.613
I really appreciate you coming
to this showcase yourself

12:59.696 --> 13:01.364
and not just sending
an associate.

13:01.448 --> 13:03.533
You won't be sorry.
Alfie's the best.

13:03.617 --> 13:04.701
- [knocking]
- Don't come in!

13:04.784 --> 13:06.328
I said don't come in.

13:06.411 --> 13:07.537
Midge Maisel is here.

13:07.621 --> 13:09.080
[quietly] Now? She's early.

13:09.164 --> 13:11.875
Uh, so I'll see you
Friday night, Mr. Glatter.

13:11.958 --> 13:13.543
Thank you. Tell Midge to wait.

13:13.627 --> 13:14.544
I'm here.

13:14.628 --> 13:15.545
I need her to wait!

13:15.629 --> 13:17.172
- Could you step outside?
- Really?

13:17.255 --> 13:19.216
She's already in. Let her stay.

13:19.299 --> 13:21.635
- [crying]
- Why is she crying?

13:21.718 --> 13:22.969
Why are you here?

13:23.053 --> 13:24.638
- We had an appointment.
- At 1:00.

13:24.721 --> 13:27.390
No, at 11:00, and it's noon,
so I'm an hour late.

13:27.474 --> 13:29.935
I told her 11:00 so she'd be
here at noon! You said,

13:30.018 --> 13:32.020
"That fucking Miriam, she's
always an hour fucking late

13:32.103 --> 13:33.939
because she doesn't give a shit
about anyone but herself!"

13:34.022 --> 13:36.149
Thank you!
And I didn't say that!

13:36.233 --> 13:37.984
Well, you're here. Sit.

13:38.068 --> 13:40.820
Because I actually have a happy
piece of news to share with you.

13:40.904 --> 13:42.572
Happy news. I'm all ears.

13:42.656 --> 13:43.990
Took a lot of string-pulling,

13:44.074 --> 13:45.951
but you said
you wanted a headlining gig.

13:46.034 --> 13:47.452
I got you a headlining gig.

13:47.536 --> 13:48.453
Are you kidding?

13:48.537 --> 13:49.704
Thousand-seat theater.

13:49.788 --> 13:50.830
Good pay, too.

13:50.914 --> 13:52.249
Amazing. Where's the gig?

13:52.332 --> 13:53.416
Croatia.

13:53.500 --> 13:55.085
Where is that, Pennsylvania?

13:55.168 --> 13:57.420
The Republic of Croatia.
That's where the gig is.

13:57.504 --> 13:59.756
The name of the place
is in their language,

13:59.839 --> 14:03.843
which loosely translates
as "Make Laugh Showing Teeth."

14:03.927 --> 14:04.844
Croatia?

14:04.928 --> 14:06.638
Uh, specifically Zagreb.

14:06.721 --> 14:07.764
I think that's the capital.

14:07.847 --> 14:09.849
- [Dinah] It is!
- Thank you!

14:09.933 --> 14:11.476
It's a five-night stand,

14:11.560 --> 14:13.979
but the place only turns on its
electricity one night a week.

14:14.062 --> 14:15.564
So you would fly in
for that one night,

14:15.647 --> 14:17.649
do the gig, then fly back.
Then you wait six days

14:17.732 --> 14:19.651
and you fly back into Zagreb,
do another gig,

14:19.734 --> 14:21.319
- and then fly back.
- For five straight weeks?

14:21.403 --> 14:22.904
Now, you're gonna need shots.

14:22.988 --> 14:24.864
Uh, smallpox, tetanus,
diphtheria.

14:24.948 --> 14:26.950
Apparently
it's excruciatingly painful,

14:27.033 --> 14:28.577
so you want to get 'em
about a week before you go.

14:28.660 --> 14:30.787
Susie, I can't do all
that traveling back and forth

14:30.870 --> 14:32.747
to a far-off country
for one show a week.

14:32.831 --> 14:33.915
I'll drop dead.

14:33.999 --> 14:35.083
No, not if you get your shots.

14:35.166 --> 14:37.085
Pass.

14:38.712 --> 14:40.422
You said, "Make me a headliner."

14:40.505 --> 14:41.923
In the Western Hemisphere.

14:42.007 --> 14:44.217
- So it's a no.
- It's a million noes.

14:44.301 --> 14:46.428
So you'll warm up for Sophie
Lennon, but you won't take this?

14:46.511 --> 14:48.680
That was a mistake
that I won't make again.

14:48.763 --> 14:50.432
You know, I don't think
I can do better than this.

14:50.515 --> 14:52.434
Do you understand?
I mean, just last week,

14:52.517 --> 14:54.436
I had a pretty big guy
angling to check you out.

14:54.519 --> 14:56.104
I didn't even have a place
to send him to see you.

14:56.187 --> 14:57.105
Who?

14:57.188 --> 14:58.356
You ever heard of Gordon Ford?

14:58.440 --> 15:00.442
Really?
Gordon Ford would come see me?

15:00.525 --> 15:01.610
Yes. Well, no, not him.

15:01.693 --> 15:03.069
He's too big. But his booker.

15:03.153 --> 15:05.614
His booker? Well, that's
still pretty big, his booker.

15:05.697 --> 15:07.866
...'s intern.
His booker's intern.

15:07.949 --> 15:10.160
But he was really into it.
And he reports to the booker,

15:10.243 --> 15:11.786
and the booker reports
to Gordon Ford.

15:11.870 --> 15:13.580
Fine. If they really want to see
me, they can always come over...

15:13.663 --> 15:15.123
Before you finish
that goddamn sentence,

15:15.206 --> 15:18.460
these guys cannot come to an
illegal strip club to see you.

15:18.543 --> 15:19.919
They're too legit.
They can't be seen there,

15:20.003 --> 15:21.421
so they just won't do it.

15:21.504 --> 15:24.174
And there is no local
headlining gig for you.

15:24.257 --> 15:25.717
Not in the near future.

15:25.800 --> 15:28.136
I am working on it,
but let's be realistic.

15:28.219 --> 15:29.721
- I'm going to lunch.
- Good.

15:29.804 --> 15:31.181
Go. Take a handkerchief.

15:32.515 --> 15:33.933
- What's the matter with her?
- [sighs]

15:34.017 --> 15:37.103
Long story. Just don't make
friends, 'cause she's got to go.

15:37.187 --> 15:38.355
Oh. Poor thing.

15:38.438 --> 15:40.398
She's not professional,
you know?

15:40.482 --> 15:41.816
She's got these boyfriends
she's always fighting with,

15:41.900 --> 15:44.319
and her tiny family's
always running around.

15:44.402 --> 15:47.155
Too much drama,
too much trouble. A lot of snot.

15:47.238 --> 15:49.074
Well, I was gonna get the Alfie
showcase info from her.

15:49.157 --> 15:50.450
I'm bringing four with me.

15:50.533 --> 15:51.785
Just grab a flyer.
It's underneath that pile.

15:51.868 --> 15:53.953
- Which one?
- The one on the right.

15:54.037 --> 15:55.872
Not that one. Next to it.

15:55.955 --> 15:57.207
The other next to it.

15:57.290 --> 15:59.167
You glued to your seat
or something? Show me.

15:59.250 --> 16:01.753
- It's right there.
- Why aren't you standing?

16:03.046 --> 16:04.130
Susie?

16:04.214 --> 16:06.383
I'm not wearing pants.

16:06.466 --> 16:07.884
Really?

16:07.967 --> 16:09.594
No, I just thought I'd do
some light comedy for you.

16:09.678 --> 16:10.845
Yes, really.

16:10.929 --> 16:12.555
Well, so what?
I've seen you in your boxers.

16:12.639 --> 16:13.890
Um...

16:13.973 --> 16:16.142
I'm not wearing boxers.

16:16.226 --> 16:17.477
You're just...

16:17.560 --> 16:19.270
- naked down there?
- Yes.

16:19.354 --> 16:20.689
Don't you stick to the seat?

16:20.772 --> 16:22.190
It wasn't a choice.

16:22.273 --> 16:24.067
The phone rang,
Dinah wasn't in yet,

16:24.150 --> 16:25.402
and I wasn't done dressing.

16:25.485 --> 16:27.904
- But...
- Get all your questions
out now!

16:27.987 --> 16:30.699
You dress yourself completely
on the top, then do the bottom?

16:30.782 --> 16:31.825
- [phone ringing]
- Yes.

16:31.908 --> 16:33.660
And not, like,
start with underwear

16:33.743 --> 16:35.704
on top and bottom
and then move on to outerwear?

16:35.787 --> 16:38.289
- No.
- Susie Myerson and Associates.

16:38.373 --> 16:39.791
May I ask who's calling?

16:39.874 --> 16:41.000
Who is it, Nicky?

16:42.043 --> 16:44.879
It's Sandy Bishop
at McCormick/Hatlestad.

16:44.963 --> 16:45.964
Oh, hi, Midge.

16:46.047 --> 16:47.799
I have to take this.

16:47.882 --> 16:50.093
Submit the rest of
your questions in writing, okay?

16:50.176 --> 16:51.886
- I'll talk to you later.
- Close the door

16:51.970 --> 16:52.929
on your way out.

16:53.012 --> 16:54.973
Hey! Miriam!

16:55.056 --> 16:57.183
- Mr. Bishop, hello.
- Midge. Long time no see.

16:57.267 --> 16:59.269
Hi, Frank. You guys helping out?

16:59.352 --> 17:01.146
- Whenever we can.
- Yeah, we hooked her up

17:01.229 --> 17:02.647
- with this place, you know.
- I know.

17:02.731 --> 17:04.566
And she's very happy here.

17:04.649 --> 17:06.443
So, uh, you taking
the Croatia gig?

17:06.526 --> 17:07.610
At Make Laugh Showing Teeth.

17:07.694 --> 17:09.154
- Uh, no.
- [Nicky] Really?

17:09.237 --> 17:11.614
- It's a thousand-seater.
Headliner.
- With electricity.

17:11.698 --> 17:13.158
I can't take it
for many reasons,

17:13.241 --> 17:15.118
but, for one, I can't leave
the kids that long.

17:15.201 --> 17:17.495
Ah. So it's a family thing.

17:17.579 --> 17:18.580
Mainly.

17:18.663 --> 17:23.001
Okay. "Not taking
due to family."

17:23.084 --> 17:24.085
You keeping track?

17:24.169 --> 17:26.671
Well, you're part
of our family now, right?

17:26.755 --> 17:30.216
Oh. Sure. I mean, my immediate
family's growing by the second,

17:30.300 --> 17:32.010
- so why not?
- Miriam,

17:32.093 --> 17:35.138
unless I'm mistaken,

17:35.221 --> 17:36.723
are you expecting?

17:36.806 --> 17:38.600
You're glowin'
but you're not showin'.

17:38.683 --> 17:41.895
No. My husband
and his mysterious girlfriend

17:41.978 --> 17:43.396
are expecting, and... [inhales]

17:43.480 --> 17:44.814
it's gonna be complicated.

17:44.898 --> 17:45.899
Mysterious, huh?

17:45.982 --> 17:47.066
He hardly knows her.

17:47.150 --> 17:48.318
Mm. Worrisome.

17:48.401 --> 17:50.403
[Susie] At Cherry Lane.
Part of the Village.

17:51.529 --> 17:52.739
Midge,

17:52.822 --> 17:54.240
you worried about this girl?

17:54.324 --> 17:55.366
No.

17:55.450 --> 17:56.701
I mean...

17:56.785 --> 17:57.952
maybe a little.

17:58.036 --> 17:59.287
She's gonna be stepmother
to your children.

17:59.370 --> 18:00.955
And play an important role
in their upbringing.

18:01.039 --> 18:02.207
Joel didn't want to hear that.

18:02.290 --> 18:03.416
Mm-hmm.

18:04.417 --> 18:05.627
Anything else?

18:07.045 --> 18:08.671
Uh...

18:09.672 --> 18:11.216
Guess not.

18:12.258 --> 18:13.426
You want us
to look into this girl?

18:13.510 --> 18:15.136
No. No, no.

18:15.220 --> 18:16.137
Could you?

18:16.221 --> 18:17.180
- We could.
- Discreetly.

18:17.263 --> 18:18.181
Or not.

18:18.264 --> 18:20.016
No, I'd want it to be discreet.

18:20.099 --> 18:21.351
If I wanted it.

18:21.434 --> 18:22.685
Well, you're talking
to the right guys.

18:22.769 --> 18:24.229
We're good at getting
information out of people.

18:24.312 --> 18:25.480
- About people.
- About people.

18:25.563 --> 18:26.564
Without them knowing.

18:27.607 --> 18:28.650
Okay.

18:29.734 --> 18:31.069
Want to give us a name?

18:31.152 --> 18:32.987
I mean, she
probably just goes to school,

18:33.071 --> 18:35.114
- goes home...
- Maybe.

18:35.198 --> 18:37.450
Maybe not.

18:40.286 --> 18:41.788
And all you need's a name?

18:43.039 --> 18:45.166
And we will be very discreet.

18:50.380 --> 18:51.673
- [wind blowing]
- [cheering]

18:51.756 --> 18:53.132
[Aunt Em] Quick! Dorothy!

18:53.216 --> 18:55.301
Run for the cellar!

18:55.385 --> 18:58.137
[cheering]

18:58.221 --> 18:59.931
[cow moos]

19:00.932 --> 19:03.393
[cackling]

19:03.476 --> 19:04.602
[Toto barking]

19:04.686 --> 19:06.521
She told Boise right
to his face--

19:06.604 --> 19:08.857
Boise runs the place--
"You knock first."

19:08.940 --> 19:11.359
"Girls have knockers. Men
knock." That's what she said.

19:11.442 --> 19:13.736
Midge has always been
quietly assertive.

19:13.820 --> 19:15.196
One of the many reasons
why I love her.

19:15.280 --> 19:17.866
I worked a place in Philly once.
Had to put a sign on the door.

19:17.949 --> 19:18.867
"No BJs."

19:18.950 --> 19:20.910
[laughing]

19:20.994 --> 19:22.453
So funny. [inhales]

19:22.537 --> 19:23.663
What's a BJ?

19:23.746 --> 19:26.249
God, honey,
you are so sweet and innocent.

19:26.332 --> 19:28.084
Like an elf
riding a bunny rabbit.

19:28.167 --> 19:30.044
Well, I love this.
Sitting around, chatting,

19:30.128 --> 19:31.337
just us working girls.

19:31.421 --> 19:32.797
Oh, you work, sweetie?
What do you do?

19:32.881 --> 19:33.965
Something with ice skates,
right?

19:34.048 --> 19:35.258
No, I can't skate.

19:35.341 --> 19:37.176
I'm a mom. Plus I'm halfway
through my studies

19:37.260 --> 19:39.012
at the Katharine Gibbs
Secretarial School.

19:39.095 --> 19:42.181
- Secretarial school?
- Oh, I'd never want
to be a secretary.

19:42.265 --> 19:43.725
Men don't respect 'em.

19:43.808 --> 19:45.935
They spend all day at the office
just staring at their tits.

19:46.019 --> 19:48.104
- It's degrading.
- Right. Well,

19:48.187 --> 19:49.856
I would definitely avoid
having them do that.

19:49.939 --> 19:51.357
You really should learn
to skate.

19:51.441 --> 19:53.693
- What's up, party pooper?
- Just finished.

19:53.776 --> 19:55.778
With payday tomorrow,
I think I am just gonna make it

19:55.862 --> 19:57.572
- this month.
- Did I tell you Archie's sorry?

19:57.655 --> 19:59.157
- He feels so awful.
- I know.

19:59.240 --> 20:01.451
He put in an order to buy
56 pieces of Tupperware from me.

20:01.534 --> 20:03.453
It's ridiculous.
I'm not calling it in.

20:03.536 --> 20:05.371
He's Archie. He's trying to pay
you back whatever way he can.

20:05.455 --> 20:06.414
We'll get through it.

20:06.497 --> 20:07.790
Money comes, money goes.

20:07.874 --> 20:10.460
It mostly goes these days,
but que será.

20:10.543 --> 20:11.586
Everything okay?

20:11.669 --> 20:13.713
Yeah. We're just talking
about the big snatch.

20:13.796 --> 20:14.964
Who? Trixie?

20:15.048 --> 20:16.424
No. Imogene's husband

20:16.507 --> 20:18.134
got a bag snatched
off the street.

20:18.217 --> 20:19.302
Had some valuables in it.

20:19.385 --> 20:20.678
The valuables belonged
to my ex-husband,

20:20.762 --> 20:22.972
who now cannot make
his monthly payment.

20:23.056 --> 20:25.558
Oh, shoot, I forgot. I've got
a lead for you on a gig, Midge.

20:25.642 --> 20:27.393
- Hmm?
- You've heard
of John F. Kennedy?

20:27.477 --> 20:29.187
- Name rings a bell.
- My dad told me

20:29.270 --> 20:31.189
there's a big New York
fundraiser for him coming up.

20:31.272 --> 20:32.565
Wives For Kennedy.

20:32.649 --> 20:33.608
Jackie's throwing it.

20:33.691 --> 20:34.984
Jackie? Jackie Kennedy?

20:35.068 --> 20:36.778
Oh, my God. I want to be
her very best friend!

20:36.861 --> 20:38.404
She's John F. Kennedy's wife.

20:38.488 --> 20:39.989
- Her name rings a bell, too.
- They need a comedian.

20:40.073 --> 20:41.824
One that looks like a lady.

20:41.908 --> 20:43.993
It was Jackie's request.
A lady comedian.

20:44.077 --> 20:45.244
'Cause it's all ladies.

20:45.328 --> 20:47.038
- Does it pay?
- Who the hell cares?

20:47.121 --> 20:48.414
Kennedy. She'll do it!

20:48.498 --> 20:50.500
It pays.
You just can't say dirty stuff.

20:50.583 --> 20:51.501
She won't. She'll do it.

20:51.584 --> 20:53.086
I'll do it. Thanks, Gloria.

20:53.169 --> 20:54.545
I'll jot down the number
to call.

20:54.629 --> 20:56.839
[cheering in distance]

20:56.923 --> 20:58.424
So how's your dad involved
in this?

20:58.508 --> 20:59.717
Oh, he's a senator.

20:59.801 --> 21:01.761
- A senator?
- Yep.

21:01.844 --> 21:02.762
I don't get it.

21:02.845 --> 21:04.180
Are you not familiar

21:04.263 --> 21:06.391
with our bicameral system
of legislature?

21:06.474 --> 21:09.477
- No, I am.
- Because you didn't seem that
familiar with John F. Kennedy.

21:09.560 --> 21:11.771
Thanks for the tip, Gloria.

21:11.854 --> 21:13.940
Come on. Dorothy must be close
to throwing up by now.

21:14.023 --> 21:16.109
Hey, introduce me
to the Big Snatch.

21:19.570 --> 21:21.572
[indistinct chatter]

21:22.615 --> 21:24.283
This is gonna be a disaster.

21:24.367 --> 21:26.494
What are you talking about?
You got a great turnout.

21:26.577 --> 21:29.163
- The bigs showed up.
- Two of 'em bailed
at the last second.

21:29.247 --> 21:30.957
Two guys out of what, 20?

21:31.040 --> 21:32.500
You did Alfie proud.

21:32.583 --> 21:34.002
Yeah, well,
I can't showcase you in a place

