33:11.949 --> 33:13.659
Her family?
Those are dangerous people.

33:13.742 --> 33:15.202
You don't fuck
with those people.

33:15.285 --> 33:17.413
They'll just disappear you.
Like you never existed at all.

33:17.496 --> 33:19.331
- Oh! Aah!
- Aah!

33:19.415 --> 33:21.750
- [screams]
- Julie, hi.
Sorry to startle you.

33:21.834 --> 33:23.043
Was that a gun?

33:23.127 --> 33:25.671
Yes, but it's a comedy gun.

33:25.754 --> 33:27.923
- Right?
- Yeah, a comedy gun.

33:28.006 --> 33:30.884
- Frank here is
my sometimes comedy partner.
- Like on the weekends.

33:30.968 --> 33:32.594
- The gun shoots
flowers out of it.
- It's a very funny gun.

33:32.678 --> 33:34.555
Sorry to startle you.

33:34.638 --> 33:37.057
You really should stop stalking
around this hallway, Miriam.

33:37.141 --> 33:39.309
You're right. I will stop.

33:39.393 --> 33:41.770
- Good night, Julie.
- Good night, Julie.

33:44.064 --> 33:46.066
Look, the less you know
about this girl's family,

33:46.150 --> 33:49.069
the better, and please
do not tell anyone

33:49.153 --> 33:50.946
we were snooping around them.
Anyone.

33:51.029 --> 33:52.573
- It didn't happen.
- Okay.

33:52.656 --> 33:54.825
And apologize to Julie for me.

33:54.908 --> 33:57.077
What happened here was
unprofessional.

33:57.161 --> 33:59.163
- I will.
- Okay.

34:06.837 --> 34:08.922
It's off to the races.

34:09.006 --> 34:12.509
A jaunty
Oleg Cassini flax helmet

34:12.593 --> 34:14.720
accessorizes this mischievous

34:14.803 --> 34:16.597
tri-colored dress.

34:16.680 --> 34:20.434
A black scroll resembling
the work of a Zen master

34:20.517 --> 34:24.062
accentuates the vertical
romanticism of this dress.

34:24.146 --> 34:26.815
The Lilly Daché hat is the icing

34:26.899 --> 34:29.276
on this tasty cake.

34:29.359 --> 34:31.445
And finally, pomegranate

34:31.528 --> 34:34.656
polka dots weave
through rectangular cutouts

34:34.740 --> 34:38.035
as a peekaboo bodice
frames the modified boatneck.

34:38.118 --> 34:40.287
A chic version
of a fisherman's rain hat

34:40.370 --> 34:42.414
completes the ensemble.

34:49.004 --> 34:50.839
And now for this afternoon's
entertainment,

34:50.923 --> 34:53.801
we have a very funny lady
who is going to tell some jokes,

34:53.884 --> 34:56.970
and then we'll have cake
from Gino's Pastry Shop.

34:57.054 --> 34:59.097
May I introduce to you,

34:59.181 --> 35:01.225
Mrs. Miriam Maisel.

35:01.308 --> 35:03.602
[audience applauds]

35:08.732 --> 35:10.526
[exhales]

35:10.609 --> 35:13.487
John F. Kennedy is
running for president.

35:14.488 --> 35:16.949
I know. It's great.

35:17.032 --> 35:19.701
Right?
We'll have a young, smart,

35:19.785 --> 35:22.204
handsome president,
and, boy, is he gonna be busy.

35:22.287 --> 35:24.122
Have you read his platform yet?

35:24.206 --> 35:26.083
He's got a six-point health care
plan that includes everything

35:26.166 --> 35:28.919
from building new hospitals
to spiffier paper gowns

35:29.002 --> 35:30.629
and turning the heat on
so you don't freeze

35:30.712 --> 35:32.172
your tush off
in the examining room.

35:32.256 --> 35:33.215
[laughter]

35:33.298 --> 35:34.758
He's gonna give
more money to NASA

35:34.842 --> 35:36.844
and we are gonna send
a man to the moon

35:36.927 --> 35:38.846
before the Soviets.

35:38.929 --> 35:41.098
All these things
sound wonderful.

35:41.181 --> 35:43.141
What could possibly be
the downside of him winning?

35:43.225 --> 35:45.686
What should we,
every single woman in this room,

35:45.769 --> 35:48.647
be very, very afraid of?

35:51.692 --> 35:53.485
- This.
- [laughter]

35:53.569 --> 35:57.364
If he wins, this is going
to be the first lady.

35:57.447 --> 35:59.157
Can you imagine, you wake up,

35:59.241 --> 36:02.119
your hair in curlers,
pillow creases on your face,

36:02.202 --> 36:04.204
and you sit down at the table
and pick this up,

36:04.288 --> 36:06.498
and see that face
first thing in the morning?

36:06.582 --> 36:09.251
I mean, really, is that fair?

36:09.334 --> 36:12.462
And it's not just the face
or the clothes or the poise--

36:12.546 --> 36:13.797
I mean, didn't they invent
the word "poise"

36:13.881 --> 36:15.007
just to describe this woman?

36:15.090 --> 36:17.634
Can you picture Jackie Kennedy

36:17.718 --> 36:19.136
having a bad hair day?

36:19.219 --> 36:20.596
Or chipped nail polish?

36:20.679 --> 36:22.931
Can you imagine her
with mustard on her shirt?

36:23.015 --> 36:25.893
Or with cramps? Now, Pat Nixon,
that woman has cramps.

36:25.976 --> 36:27.561
Probably every single day.

36:27.644 --> 36:29.730
I'm sure Pat's a very nice lady,

36:29.813 --> 36:31.356
but I feel like I know
what she looks like

36:31.440 --> 36:33.233
after a night with her in-laws.

36:33.317 --> 36:35.444
Exhausted, slightly drunk,

36:35.527 --> 36:37.905
full of resentment,
and suddenly realizing

36:37.988 --> 36:40.032
the ice pick can be used
on something other than ice.

36:40.115 --> 36:42.409
But not Jackie.

36:42.492 --> 36:44.369
Her in-laws love her.

36:44.453 --> 36:47.039
They eat her roast
and bring her flowers.

36:47.122 --> 36:49.124
She's fluent in French, Spanish

36:49.207 --> 36:50.542
and Italian and Yiddish.

36:50.626 --> 36:51.960
Okay, I have no proof
about the last one,

36:52.044 --> 36:53.295
but I still believe it's true.

36:53.378 --> 36:56.173
- [laughter]
- Do we really want a first lady

36:56.256 --> 36:58.091
who looks like this on a horse?

36:58.175 --> 36:59.968
Or do we want a first lady

37:00.052 --> 37:02.012
who looks a little more
like the horse?

37:02.095 --> 37:03.472
I mean an attractive horse.

37:03.555 --> 37:05.182
I'm talking Buttermilk,
not Trigger.

37:06.433 --> 37:08.685
- We women are dealing
with a lot.
- [woman] Right.

37:08.769 --> 37:10.562
Do we really need
to be constantly comparing

37:10.646 --> 37:13.565
ourselves...
Oh, come on!

37:13.649 --> 37:16.443
Who has that kind
of perfect facial expression

37:16.526 --> 37:18.195
while they're at the beach?

37:18.278 --> 37:20.697
Where's the sunburn?
The sweat stains?

37:20.781 --> 37:23.033
Where's the grape soda stain
from her daughter

37:23.116 --> 37:24.743
throwing up on her
after the first time

37:24.826 --> 37:26.703
she swung her around
in the ocean?

37:26.787 --> 37:28.747
Where is the look
on Jackie's face that says,

37:28.830 --> 37:30.707
"If I just let go right now..."

37:30.791 --> 37:32.292
[audience clamoring]

37:32.376 --> 37:34.002
She is absolutely perfect.

37:34.086 --> 37:36.213
Here's a charming,
little anecdote.

37:36.296 --> 37:37.589
"When the senator lost the notes

37:37.673 --> 37:38.966
for a speech
which he had planned

37:39.049 --> 37:41.009
to end with a quote
from Tennyson's Ulysses,

37:41.093 --> 37:43.428
Jackie bailed him out of trouble
by quickly reciting

37:43.512 --> 37:44.930
the appropriate lines
from memory."

37:45.013 --> 37:46.932
[audience] Oh...

37:47.015 --> 37:48.934
Who are you?!

37:49.017 --> 37:50.852
That was Pat Nixon asking,

37:50.936 --> 37:52.729
not me.

37:52.813 --> 37:54.773
That's a cute outfit.

37:54.856 --> 37:56.692
That's cute, too.
Sorry, I'm just shopping now.

37:56.775 --> 37:58.402
You know,

37:58.485 --> 38:00.404
I used to have a dress
like this.

38:00.487 --> 38:01.989
Called it my lucky dress.

38:02.072 --> 38:04.074
And it was until... well,

38:04.157 --> 38:06.243
that's a story for another time.

38:06.326 --> 38:08.954
[audience clamoring]

38:09.037 --> 38:11.081
Nope, wrong venue.
It's a little racy.

38:11.164 --> 38:13.792
There's baby carrots here.

38:13.875 --> 38:16.086
We'll cover them up
with the mashed potatoes.

38:19.006 --> 38:20.257
All right.

38:20.340 --> 38:22.342
[audience cheering]

38:24.219 --> 38:27.514
Well, I am recently divorced.

38:27.597 --> 38:29.474
And a little lonely.

38:29.558 --> 38:31.351
And a couple weeks ago,
I meet this man.

38:31.435 --> 38:33.437
He seemed really nice,
very handsome,

38:33.520 --> 38:35.522
and I was in my lucky dress.
Perfect combo.

38:35.605 --> 38:38.275
So we go for coffee,
but the coffee place is closed.

38:38.358 --> 38:40.777
And so he suggests a little
coffee at his apartment.

38:40.861 --> 38:43.447
Anyhow, he was out of coffee,
so we had sex.

38:43.530 --> 38:46.033
- [audience gasping]
- Now, I know
what you're thinking.

38:46.116 --> 38:48.201
He didn't have tea? Soda?

38:48.285 --> 38:50.162
Fruit can be hydrating.
How about an apple?

38:50.245 --> 38:51.872
The only other option was sex?

38:51.955 --> 38:53.999
Yes. It's my story,
so deal with it.

38:54.082 --> 38:57.961
So we had sex and it was great.

38:58.045 --> 39:00.213
When suddenly
the door flies open,

39:00.297 --> 39:02.674
and this crazed woman comes in
with a little dog

39:02.758 --> 39:04.134
and starts yelling
and screaming,

39:04.217 --> 39:05.385
and I'm thinking,
"Who is this nut?"

39:05.469 --> 39:06.845
And I was about to suggest
we call the police

39:06.928 --> 39:08.513
until I realized
it was his wife.

39:08.597 --> 39:10.223
[audience gasping]

39:10.307 --> 39:11.933
I couldn't believe it.

39:12.017 --> 39:14.436
I was the other woman.
I was the harlot.

39:14.519 --> 39:17.314
The strumpet.
I was all the things

39:17.397 --> 39:19.149
I called my husband's mistress.

39:19.232 --> 39:21.318
Can you imagine
catching your husband

39:21.401 --> 39:23.653
with another woman in your bed?

39:23.737 --> 39:26.698
But as I was laying there,
in her bed,

39:26.782 --> 39:29.201
- under her sheets, I...
- [woman crying]

39:37.834 --> 39:40.754
Hey, look on the bright side.

39:40.837 --> 39:43.590
She got to keep my lucky dress.

39:43.673 --> 39:45.675
[women sobbing]

39:48.345 --> 39:49.721
Where's that cake?

39:49.805 --> 39:51.264
[woman sobs loudly]

39:51.348 --> 39:53.350
[phone ringing]

39:58.730 --> 40:00.357
Susie Myerson and Associates.

40:00.440 --> 40:02.400
- [Midge] Hey, got a question.
- Sure, what?

40:02.484 --> 40:04.986
So, lunch tomorrow,
Dinah told me 1:30,

40:05.070 --> 40:06.738
but is that what time lunch is,
or is that an hour before

40:06.822 --> 40:09.032
the actual lunch because she
figures I'll be an hour late?

40:09.116 --> 40:10.492
Well, if she thinks
you'll be an hour late,

40:10.575 --> 40:11.827
that means
we're meeting at 2:30.

40:11.910 --> 40:13.203
And she told me 12:45.

40:13.286 --> 40:15.080
And she knows I won't be
more than 15 minutes late

40:15.163 --> 40:16.331
'cause I'm coming
from the Upper East Side,

40:16.414 --> 40:17.374
so that doesn't make sense.

40:17.457 --> 40:18.667
And I know she schedules
these things

40:18.750 --> 40:20.460
around my being late,
so I'm already adjusting

40:20.544 --> 40:22.796
to that, so is she adjusting
to my adjustment?

40:22.879 --> 40:25.090
You know, none of this matters,
because tonight's the night.

40:25.173 --> 40:27.509
I'm taking Dinah out to dinner
so we can have the talk.

40:27.592 --> 40:29.469
I let her pick
the place and everything.

40:29.553 --> 40:30.887
Oh, the talk.

40:30.971 --> 40:32.472
Yeah, my hiring/firing book

40:32.556 --> 40:34.099
says you should show
as much respect as you can

40:34.182 --> 40:35.475
to the person you're
canning so they don't

40:35.559 --> 40:37.185
show up
and kill you or something.

40:37.269 --> 40:38.562
Okay. I'll see you tomorrow.

40:38.645 --> 40:39.855
And I'll have a little
something for you, too.

40:39.938 --> 40:41.565
A little something?
What little something?

40:41.648 --> 40:43.358
Besides a cupcake
that Ethel Kennedy touched,

40:43.441 --> 40:45.443
which makes it special, I'm
bringing your cut of the gig.

40:45.527 --> 40:47.154
- What gig?
- A gig. I picked up a gig.

40:47.237 --> 40:48.363
I didn't get you a gig.

40:48.446 --> 40:49.948
Well, it was just
a money gig I did.

40:50.031 --> 40:51.324
It falls
into the money category.

40:51.408 --> 40:52.492
I'm all dolled up.

40:52.576 --> 40:54.452
Okay, I have to go,

40:54.536 --> 40:56.163
but tomorrow
I'll be very interested

40:56.246 --> 40:58.039
in hearing
about what this gig was

40:58.123 --> 40:59.583
that you did
that I didn't book for you.

40:59.666 --> 41:02.252
- Okay, I'll see you at 1:30.
- 12:45.

41:02.335 --> 41:04.504
You clean up nice.

41:04.588 --> 41:06.381
Thanks. So do you. Shall we go?

41:06.464 --> 41:08.049
Sure, but, hey, you know what?

41:08.133 --> 41:09.718
Why don't you take
that coat that you leave here

41:09.801 --> 41:11.261
- all the time?
- Why?

41:11.344 --> 41:13.513
There's been a string of
burglaries in the neighborhood.

41:13.597 --> 41:15.056
Wouldn't want someone
to take it.

41:15.140 --> 41:17.017
Good deal.

41:17.100 --> 41:18.977
Here, I had
this bag lying around.

41:19.060 --> 41:21.521
Put your coat in the bag.

41:21.605 --> 41:24.441
You should take
these pictures, too.

41:24.524 --> 41:26.318
- Just to be safe.
- Okay.

41:26.401 --> 41:28.069
Is this something you like?

41:28.153 --> 41:29.613
My nephew made it
for me at camp.

41:29.696 --> 41:33.450
Yeah, throw that in. This, too.

41:33.533 --> 41:35.493
Okay.

41:35.577 --> 41:38.580
That is it.

41:38.663 --> 41:39.831
Let's eat.

41:39.915 --> 41:42.125
[indistinct chatter]

41:42.209 --> 41:44.044
Chicken and waffles
with collard greens?

41:44.127 --> 41:46.213
I mean, who knew this would be
an appetizing combination?

41:46.296 --> 41:48.173
Well, it's good, so someone did.

41:48.256 --> 41:49.841
I like people with a vision.

41:49.925 --> 41:51.092
Listen, Dinah...

41:51.176 --> 41:52.719
Damn, there's Hank.
Scoot to the right.

41:52.802 --> 41:54.221
- Why?
- To block him.

41:54.304 --> 41:56.514
- Fine.
- Little more.

41:56.598 --> 41:59.309
- Little more, little more,
little more, little more, stop!
- You good?

41:59.392 --> 42:00.685
- I'm good.
- Okay.

42:00.769 --> 42:02.103
So, Dinah, I want to make sure

42:02.187 --> 42:03.521
you're happy in this job,

42:03.605 --> 42:05.398
'cause if you're not,
we need to talk.

42:05.482 --> 42:06.691
Oh, I'm happy.

42:06.775 --> 42:08.735
- You don't seem it.
- I'm super happy.

42:08.818 --> 42:10.779
I'm happier than I've ever been
in my whole life.

42:10.862 --> 42:13.698
Had a toy dog made of wood when
I was a kid. You pull the leash

42:13.782 --> 42:15.700
and he wags his tail and walks
and his eyes move?

42:15.784 --> 42:17.869
That brought me a ton of joy.
This is better.

42:17.953 --> 42:20.580
Right, but as your employer,
I need to be happy, as well.

42:20.664 --> 42:22.165
I'm trying to picture you happy.

42:22.249 --> 42:23.750
It's a struggle.

42:23.833 --> 42:25.961
Yeah, maybe I don't get skip-
around, all-happy-pappy happy,

42:26.044 --> 42:28.046
but I am talking
satisfied employer happy.

42:28.129 --> 42:29.589
See, I have to constantly be...

42:29.673 --> 42:32.467
Hey, hey, sorry, y'all.
Dinner's ruined. James is here.

42:32.550 --> 42:34.719
- Are you kidding me?
- I didn't bring you here
for chicken and waffles.

42:34.803 --> 42:36.179
I brought you here to see James.

42:36.263 --> 42:37.722
That's right.
It's a comedian doing comedy.

42:37.806 --> 42:39.683
- Dinah...
- Comedy being

42:39.766 --> 42:40.892
the only way
a Black man can kill

42:40.976 --> 42:42.269
and have
a room full of white people

42:42.352 --> 42:43.561
tell him, "Good job."

42:43.645 --> 42:44.813
[man] Sit down, James.

42:44.896 --> 42:46.314
[James] Brother, you look
like you killed somebody.

42:46.398 --> 42:48.316
Look, I killed somebody, too,
so on the count of three,

42:48.400 --> 42:49.985
let's both say who we killed.

42:50.068 --> 42:51.903
Don't worry,
nobody's listening anyway.

42:51.987 --> 42:53.697
One, two, three.

42:53.780 --> 42:55.031
Bing Crosby.

42:55.115 --> 42:58.451
Welched on a golf bet,
so I smoked his ass.

42:58.535 --> 43:00.287
We got some folks
at the lunch counter right now,

43:00.370 --> 43:01.871
they're protesting me
still talking.

43:01.955 --> 43:03.957
He's super clumsy,
but I think he's funny.

43:04.040 --> 43:05.458
[James] Look,
I'm trying to be nice.

43:05.542 --> 43:07.919
My mama always said
you get more with sugar

43:08.003 --> 43:09.879
than you get with vinegar.

43:09.963 --> 43:12.299
I guess that's why
she only got her left foot now,

43:12.382 --> 43:13.383
'cause of all that sugar.

43:13.466 --> 43:14.759
[both laugh]

43:14.843 --> 43:16.678
Yeah, I figured folks with
diabetes wouldn't laugh at that,

43:16.761 --> 43:19.097
so I just learned a whole lot
about you all here.

43:19.180 --> 43:21.266
Hey, hey, pour some more
syrup on that shit, brother.

43:21.349 --> 43:23.435
My mama would kill me

43:23.518 --> 43:25.312
if she knew
I was doing this tonight.

43:25.395 --> 43:27.439
She worked her whole life
to keep me out of danger,

43:27.522 --> 43:29.733
and here I am doing the most
dangerous thing you can do--

43:29.816 --> 43:31.484
interrupt Black folks
while they eat.

43:31.568 --> 43:34.404
You know, I'm actually trying to
get beyond the Negro audience.

43:34.487 --> 43:36.531
Because everything's
aimed at white people.

43:36.614 --> 43:38.491
I mean,
that's where the money is.

43:38.575 --> 43:40.493
I mean,
think about children's stories.

43:40.577 --> 43:42.162
If Hansel and Gretel were Black,

43:42.245 --> 43:44.789
that story would be four lines.

43:44.873 --> 43:47.459
The kids leave cornbread crumbs
to follow their tracks.

43:47.542 --> 43:49.336
The witch catches
up to 'em and say,

43:49.419 --> 43:50.795
"What's that cornbread recipe?"

43:50.879 --> 43:52.714
Together they make the greatest
cornbread of all time.

43:52.797 --> 43:55.592
She forgets to eat 'em,
end of story.

43:55.675 --> 43:58.595
- Black Beauty, yeah...
- You found this guy?

43:58.678 --> 44:00.305
Yeah, I've seen him twice.
He just seems special.

44:00.388 --> 44:02.265
- [James] Thank you,
Anna Sewell...
- Yeah.

44:02.349 --> 44:03.933
- He is.
- [man] Don't quit your day job.

44:04.017 --> 44:06.853
You know, I-I don't just play
at smelly restaurants.

44:06.936 --> 44:10.482
I also play a wide range
of upscale lavatories

44:10.565 --> 44:12.942
- all across the tristate area.
- [man] Where my pork chop at?

44:13.026 --> 44:15.028
- Hey, Junior!
- Hey, James.

44:15.111 --> 44:17.489
Dinah Ruttles. What's up?

44:17.572 --> 44:19.449
This is Susie.
I told you about her.

44:19.532 --> 44:21.534
Refresh my memory.

44:21.618 --> 44:23.578
- I'm a talent manager.
- All right.

44:23.661 --> 44:25.246
Look, I think
you're funny as hell.

44:25.330 --> 44:27.290
- But...
- What?

44:27.374 --> 44:29.042
There's always
a "but" with you people.

44:29.125 --> 44:30.168
Don't do that.

44:30.251 --> 44:32.212
Okay, fair enough,
here's the but.

44:32.295 --> 44:33.963
But you got lousy segues.

44:34.047 --> 44:36.091
Yeah, I know
I've got some segue issues.

44:36.174 --> 44:38.051
And you meander.
You got a lot of topics.

44:38.134 --> 44:40.136
- Too many.
- Well, I got a lot
of things on my mind.

44:40.220 --> 44:41.638
Good. Hone it.

44:41.721 --> 44:43.098
Anything else?

44:43.181 --> 44:45.975
- You got management?
- Managers just take your money.

44:46.059 --> 44:48.436
Oh, yeah? You got a lot
of experience with managers?

44:48.520 --> 44:50.730
- I've heard things.
- Well, have you heard
that without a manager,

44:50.814 --> 44:53.024
you'll be working men's rooms
for the next ten years?

44:53.108 --> 44:55.235
She full of shit?

44:55.318 --> 44:57.028
- Not about this.
- I want to manage you.

44:57.112 --> 44:58.822
Let's try it for six months.

44:58.905 --> 45:01.449
See if, at the very least, I can
get you into better bathrooms.

45:02.826 --> 45:04.536
You got a card?

45:04.619 --> 45:06.621
Hmm.

45:07.872 --> 45:09.416
Take a fry.

45:09.499 --> 45:11.584
Call me tomorrow.
I'll buy you lunch.

45:14.629 --> 45:16.631
Later, James.

45:18.383 --> 45:19.884
I should get home.

45:19.968 --> 45:22.262
My mama gets worried
when I'm out and I don't call.

45:22.345 --> 45:24.180
Here, I'll take this.

45:24.264 --> 45:26.391
Oh, so I'm coming back tomorrow?

45:26.474 --> 45:28.184
Yeah. Of course you are.

45:28.268 --> 45:29.477
9:30, don't be late.

45:29.561 --> 45:31.938
Okay, just have your pants on

45:32.021 --> 45:33.523
when I get there.

45:33.606 --> 45:36.234
Yeah, I almost never
not have my pants on.

45:36.317 --> 45:38.611
- What's the purple?
- I'm guessing it's an eggplant.

45:38.695 --> 45:41.114
- Or a grape.
- [Midge] I don't want Esther
dressed as an eggplant.

45:41.197 --> 45:42.824
She doesn't want Esther
dressed as an eggplant.

45:42.907 --> 45:44.117
That's why the choices.

45:44.200 --> 45:45.994
You got your pumpkin,
you got your carrot,

45:46.077 --> 45:48.079
- you got a couple
varieties of beans.
- You hear that?

45:48.163 --> 45:50.165
A pineapple would
look cute on Esther.

45:50.248 --> 45:51.499
Any sweet fruit would
look good on her.

45:51.583 --> 45:52.709
Just don't make her savory.

45:52.792 --> 45:54.294
A sweet fruit for Esther.

45:54.377 --> 45:56.212
And Ethan'll probably want
to be a banana or a carrot.

45:56.296 --> 45:58.423
You know, those shapes
that boys are so obsessed with.

45:58.506 --> 46:00.633
- Got it, carrot for Ethan.
- [Moishe] Easy-peasy.

46:00.717 --> 46:02.844
- [Joel] So we're good to go?
- Sure.

46:02.927 --> 46:04.512
- We're good, Pop.
- I'll tell your mother.

46:04.596 --> 46:06.556
Hey, Pop, why don't you stay
and have a quick drink?

46:06.639 --> 46:08.141
I won't say no to that.

46:08.224 --> 46:10.226
- Meet me at the bar.
- You got it.

46:12.395 --> 46:14.314
So, look, I'm telling Pop

46:14.397 --> 46:16.274
tonight about Mei.
About everything.

46:16.357 --> 46:18.276
- I'd say it's overdue.
- I know.

46:18.359 --> 46:20.069
I'm just telling you
as a courtesy.

46:20.153 --> 46:22.489
They'll probably call Abe
and Rose as soon as they hear.

46:22.572 --> 46:24.574
Okay. Thanks for the heads-up.

46:24.657 --> 46:26.159
Pineapple and carrot's good.

46:26.242 --> 46:27.577
It's gonna work.

46:27.660 --> 46:30.205
I agree. Keep me posted.

46:30.288 --> 46:32.707
[Gordon] Welcome back, you're
watching The Gordon Ford Show.

46:32.790 --> 46:35.376
And we got funny man
Lenny Bruce.

46:35.460 --> 46:38.129
So, Carnegie Hall, you nervous
about filling the place?

46:38.213 --> 46:41.174
Not until about three seconds
ago, Gordy, no.

46:41.257 --> 46:42.800
[laughs] Yeah,
but you don't have

46:42.884 --> 46:44.636
performance anxiety anymore,
do you, Lenny?

46:44.719 --> 46:46.137
[audience laughing]

46:46.221 --> 46:48.598
Wait a minute, wait a...
[laughs]

46:48.681 --> 46:51.226
Wait a minute, no, no, no,
no, you know what I meant.

46:51.309 --> 46:53.102
Now, come on, l-let's-let's
keep it clean here, folks.

46:53.186 --> 46:54.729
Nabisco's one of our sponsors.

46:54.812 --> 46:56.648
[Lenny] Hey, it's your audience
who's got the dirty mind.

46:56.731 --> 46:58.900
Mine is clean as Anita Bryant's.

46:58.983 --> 47:00.652
Well, you're gonna
fill the place.

47:00.735 --> 47:02.695
- I've got confidence in you.
- Okay, look, uh...

47:02.779 --> 47:06.282
I'm going to awkwardly shill
for myself here, Gordy.

47:06.366 --> 47:09.369
My manager made me promise,
so here goes.

47:09.452 --> 47:11.621
Uh, z-zoom in on me, guys.

47:11.704 --> 47:13.706
Uh, come on.

47:13.790 --> 47:15.750
There you go.
Oh, watch the cue card, though.

47:15.833 --> 47:17.877
All right, that's... real...
There it is.

47:17.961 --> 47:20.630
Uh... [laughs]

47:20.713 --> 47:23.716
Folks, this is Lenny Bruce.

47:23.800 --> 47:26.803
Asking you to please, please

47:26.886 --> 47:29.681
come to my show at the hall
they call Carnegie.

47:29.764 --> 47:31.641
My self-esteem is at risk here.

47:31.724 --> 47:34.936
A less-than-sold-out show
would shatter my fragile ego

47:35.019 --> 47:37.772
and hurt something very dear
to the lawyers of America,

47:37.855 --> 47:39.440
my bank account.

47:39.524 --> 47:42.402
So come to my show.

47:42.485 --> 47:45.738
And buy Nabisco products,
for Gordy's sake.

47:45.822 --> 47:47.949
I'm telling you,
dunk a Ritz Cracker

47:48.032 --> 47:51.327
in a dry whiskey... tasty, gang.

47:51.411 --> 47:52.996
[Gordon] Okay, well, how about
we get some Ritz Crackers

47:53.079 --> 47:54.872
and whiskey for everyone
in the audience, huh?

47:54.956 --> 47:57.375
[audience cheering]

47:57.417 --> 47:58.876
[♪ "Que Será, Será"]

47:58.960 --> 48:00.795
Let's clink, kiddo.
You know your mother.

48:00.878 --> 48:02.714
She's gonna want me home
at some point.

48:02.797 --> 48:05.258
[both] L'chaim.

48:05.341 --> 48:07.093
So, what's on your mind?

48:07.176 --> 48:08.970
Just wanted to have a drink
with my favorite father.

48:09.053 --> 48:10.722
Once more, with feeling.

48:10.805 --> 48:13.224
Okay. So I know I was
a little cagey before,

48:13.308 --> 48:14.767
about this girl I'm seeing.

48:14.851 --> 48:16.811
- Supposedly seeing.
- There is a girl.

48:16.894 --> 48:18.730
A great girl. The name's Mei.

48:18.813 --> 48:20.940
May? A lovely month,
a lovely name.

48:21.024 --> 48:23.234
And she is going to be a doctor.

48:23.318 --> 48:24.902
So that part is true?
Good for you.

48:24.986 --> 48:26.821
And it looks
like we're gonna get married.

48:26.904 --> 48:28.906
Yes!
We should've gotten doubles.

48:28.990 --> 48:30.366
I can fix that.

48:30.450 --> 48:33.202
Married!
Your mother's gonna plotz!

48:33.286 --> 48:35.622
But...
that's only the half of it.

48:35.705 --> 48:37.749
Only the half?
There's another half?

48:37.832 --> 48:40.126
- I'm all ears.
- Okay.

48:40.209 --> 48:42.420
I'll get your waitress. Linda?

48:42.503 --> 48:44.505
[woman singing
in foreign language]

48:50.511 --> 48:53.306
♪ Que será, será...

48:56.601 --> 48:57.518
- [woman screams]
- Shit!

48:57.602 --> 48:59.771
Pop! Pop!

48:59.854 --> 49:01.898
Call an ambulance!
Call an ambulance!

49:01.981 --> 49:03.107
Is there a doctor in the house?

49:03.191 --> 49:04.901
Any kind of doctor?

